158
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:40,006
He's definitely a pro.

159
00:05:40,073 --> 00:05:41,274
-He's a dating-show pro.
-Yes.

160
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:42,542
He heard all of it.

161
00:05:42,608 --> 00:05:43,609
I had no idea.

162
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:48,614
If you are done drawing,
show us and explain it.

163
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:52,452
-Shall we guess Sung-won's first?
-All right.

164
00:05:53,286 --> 00:05:54,921
It's too obvious.

165
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,024
-What could this be?
-It looks like you.

166
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,226
I like to draw straightforwardly.

167
00:06:00,293 --> 00:06:03,529
You want to be a sloth
and do nothing in your next life.

168
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:05,698
Did she get ity?

169
00:06:05,765 --> 00:06:06,799
Yes.

170
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:07,934
EASY PEASY

171
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,037
-But it's a little different.
-Is it?

172
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:12,705
It's not that I want to do nothing.

173
00:06:12,772 --> 00:06:14,107
-You want a slow life.
-I'd like

174
00:06:14,173 --> 00:06:15,742
a slow and leisurely life.

175
00:06:15,808 --> 00:06:18,244
Like the sloth civil servant in Zootopia.

176
00:06:18,311 --> 00:06:20,079
-The sloth civil servant.
-Yes.

177
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:22,215
BRIEFLY SHOWING OFF
SLOTH MIMICKING SKILLS

178
00:06:22,281 --> 00:06:25,084
A sloth moves at its own pace.

179
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:27,520
Just as I've lived a busy life
at a human pace,

180
00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:29,088
I could live by sloth speed

181
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:31,290
if I were born as a sloth.

182
00:06:31,824 --> 00:06:33,426
-That's a good portrait of a sloth.
-Yes.

183
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:36,062
He draws that well every time?

184
00:06:36,129 --> 00:06:37,363
-Yes.
-His drawings

185
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:40,199
are often even better than that
that you want to keep for yourself.

186
00:06:40,266 --> 00:06:42,568
We didn't draw for that long,

187
00:06:42,635 --> 00:06:44,971
but he did an amazing job. He's very good.

188
00:06:45,037 --> 00:06:46,205
Our youngest.

189
00:06:46,272 --> 00:06:47,407
Ms. Youngest.

190
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:49,342
Everyone did so well.

191
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:50,977
How cute.

192
00:06:51,844 --> 00:06:52,879
-Gosh.
-A cat.

193
00:06:52,945 --> 00:06:54,013
How cute.

194
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,448
-It's so cute.
-But…

195
00:06:55,515 --> 00:06:57,216
Look at the angle.

196
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:59,285
It's in a box and going, "Meow."

197
00:06:59,352 --> 00:07:00,353
Meow.

198
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,954
-That's what it seems.
-You're right.

199
00:07:02,021 --> 00:07:05,191
But it looks like a stray cat
rather than a rich family's cat.

200
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,259
You're right.

201
00:07:06,325 --> 00:07:09,762
But there's a reason why
I chose to draw a stray cat.

202
00:07:09,829 --> 00:07:12,799
I thought it would be better
to meet a variety of owners.

203
00:07:12,865 --> 00:07:14,567
-I see.
-I would be

204
00:07:14,634 --> 00:07:16,769
reborn as a smart cat

205
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:17,970
and make my own choice.

206
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:21,007
"The owner didn't abandon me.
I left them."

207
00:07:21,073 --> 00:07:22,575
You spelled it wrong, though.

208
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:24,510
It's "Take me" not "Taik me."

209
00:07:24,577 --> 00:07:26,946
Cats wouldn't know how to spell things.

210
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,414
IF THE PRESIDENT SAYS SO

211
00:07:28,481 --> 00:07:29,782
Oh, because I'm a cat…

212
00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:30,850
That was smart.

213
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:32,718
-It's a cat's writing.
-Yes.

214
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,287
NEXT UP

215
00:07:34,353 --> 00:07:35,955
Ji-yeon. What's that?

216
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,490
-It's a tree.
-Yes.

217
00:07:37,557 --> 00:07:38,791
