218
00:07:38,858 --> 00:07:39,859
-I know.
-Oh, my.

219
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,494
-But the leaves are different colors.
-Wow.

220
00:07:41,561 --> 00:07:43,529
Do you think you can get it?

221
00:07:43,596 --> 00:07:47,300
You want to be a big tree
that the sloth can hang onto?

222
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:49,202
NEWBIE'S KIND OF ANSWER

223
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:53,439
A big tree
that the sloth can hang onto?

224
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:54,740
I WILL BE YOUR TREE

225
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:57,009
Look at these two.

226
00:07:57,076 --> 00:07:59,378
There's a reason I want to be a tree.

227
00:07:59,445 --> 00:08:02,315
You have to accomplish something
living as a human.

228
00:08:02,381 --> 00:08:04,217
You have to make money,

229
00:08:04,283 --> 00:08:05,585
be good to your parents,

230
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:08,788
and things like that.
There are roles we have to fulfill.

231
00:08:08,855 --> 00:08:10,022
But when you become a tree,

232
00:08:10,089 --> 00:08:11,290
you blossom in the spring,

233
00:08:11,357 --> 00:08:13,259
grow leaves in the summer,

234
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,394
