00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:59,939
They're so wholesome that
I feel cleansed just by talking to them.

257
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:04,777
Everyone did such a good job
with their drawing

258
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:07,380
-that I'm embarrassed to show mine.
-You did a good job.

259
00:09:07,446 --> 00:09:09,215
Isn't that a marriage proposal?

260
00:09:09,282 --> 00:09:11,350
It looks like you're passing something on.

261
00:09:11,417 --> 00:09:14,053
You used to be the receiver,
but you want to be the giver?

262
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,488
AMAZED

263
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:16,689
Nice interpretation.

264
00:09:16,756 --> 00:09:17,924
I'll give you a hint.

265
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:20,059
You all did something you'd enjoy,
but mine is…

266
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:21,193
-Sad?
-Is it sad?

267
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:22,428
A family moment?

268
00:09:22,495 --> 00:09:24,797
ALREADY SAD

269
00:09:24,864 --> 00:09:26,265
Oh, that's it.

270
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:29,302
Since you received a lot
from your parents in this life,

271
00:09:29,368 --> 00:09:31,170
you'd like to be their parents

272
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,939
and give them
many things in your next life.

273
00:09:33,005 --> 00:09:34,373
-That's right.
-Oh, my!

274
00:09:35,841 --> 00:09:37,743
-You love your family.
-How touching.

275
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:38,811
So touching.

276
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:39,912
How did you draw it?

277
00:09:39,979 --> 00:09:41,914
-My name is Bo-ra.
-Bo-ra.

278
00:09:41,981 --> 00:09:46,586
The purple person is me,
and the yellow person is my parents.

279
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:49,355
In our next lives,
I'd like to be their parent

280
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:52,091
and I'd like them to be born
as my daughter and son.

281
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,826
That's what I'd like.

282
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:56,829
Do you think you received
a lot from your parents in this life?

283
00:09:56,896 --> 00:09:58,731
I could never repay them
for what I received.

284
00:09:58,798 --> 00:10:01,133
SO TOUCHING

285
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,202
It isn't easy to say that, right?

286
00:10:04,036 --> 00:10:07,106
-That was so touching.
-Yes.

287
00:10:07,173 --> 00:10:09,942
The fact that she thought
about her parents means

288
00:10:10,009 --> 00:10:11,177
that they are very close.

289
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:12,979
THEY'VE BECOME SOLEMN
AT THE THOUGHT OF THEIR PARENTS

290
00:10:13,045 --> 00:10:15,414
-It's your turn.
-Yes, it's my turn, isn't it?

291
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:16,482
I'm rooting for you.

292
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:20,353
I thought I ought to live
this good a life in my next life.

293
00:10:20,419 --> 00:10:21,721
Shall we try to guess?

294
00:10:23,522 --> 00:10:24,557
What's that?

295
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:25,625
FOCUSED

296
00:10:25,691 --> 00:10:27,059
If I am reborn,

297
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:29,862
I will definitely learn English.

298
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:31,631
-English? He wants to travel
-Yes. Then,

299
00:10:31,697 --> 00:10:33,099
-the world?
-I'll go to Hollywood.

300
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:37,103
I was so envious of Leonardo DiCaprio.

301
00:10:37,169 --> 00:10:39,105
He'd always rent a boat

302
00:10:39,171 --> 00:10:41,407
and throw parties on it!

303
00:10:42,008 --> 00:10:44,076
-How awesome.
-After working hard,

304
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,646
I'll have parties on my boat, fly on jets,

305
00:10:46,712 --> 00:10:48,748
and get supplies from a helicopter.

306
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,182
TITLE: PARTY ON A BOAT

307
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:51,784
-It's very specific.
-Yes.

308
00:10:51,851 --> 00:10:55,988
Of course, I am quite satisfied
with my current life as well.

309
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,523
I'm grateful for it.

310
00:10:58,124 --> 00:10:59,892
If I were to be reincarnated,

311
00:10:59,959 --> 00:11:02,628
I'd like to experience
something like this, at least.

312
00:11:02,695 --> 00:11:04,130
That's what I was thinking.

313
00:11:04,196 --> 00:11:06,232
Just like Gatsby.

314
00:11:06,298 --> 00:11:09,802
If you're going to be reborn,
you might as well live like this.

315
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:10,903
Our president is up.

316
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,905
-It's so much pressure.
-You're up, President.

317
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:15,808
You'd expect the president
to draw the best.

318
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:18,010
-But I think mine's the worst.
-No.

319
00:11:18,077 --> 00:11:20,112
-You drew so well.
-You did such a good job.

320
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,180
It's cute.

321
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:23,282
THERE, THERE
YOU DID SUCH A GREAT JOB

322
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:25,518
You did an amazing job.

323
00:11:25,584 --> 00:11:26,585
It's cute.

324
00:11:26,652 --> 00:11:29,789
When we read webtoons
or watch animated movies,

325
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:33,125
the character is hit by a car
and wakes up in an alternate universe.

326
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,226
An alternate universe.

327
00:11:34,293 --> 00:11:35,995
Maybe I could end up
in an alternate universe.

328
00:11:36,062 --> 00:11:39,532
I'd like to be the youngest daughter
who is clueless about everything

329
00:11:39,598 --> 00:11:41,033
and is doted upon.

330
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,234
YOUNGEST DAUGHTER OF A NOBLE

331
00:11:42,301 --> 00:11:43,636
A young noble lady.

332
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,371
-A young lady?
-I see.

333
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:47,406
I'd have a lovely teatime

334
00:11:47,473 --> 00:11:49,742
-and eat cakes.
-How nice.

335
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:52,645
This is my dog.
We would be reincarnated together.

336
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:55,047
He would even know how to speak.

337
00:11:55,114 --> 00:11:57,683
-It's like that in animated movies.
-Since it's an alternate universe?

338
00:11:57,750 --> 00:12:00,019
I dream about a life like that.

339
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,221
-Very nice.
-How cute.

340
00:12:02,288 --> 00:12:03,689
Most of you

341
00:12:03,756 --> 00:12:07,193
seem to want your next life
to be free of worries

342
00:12:07,259 --> 00:12:10,129
and want to live
a comfortable, relaxed life.

343
00:12:10,196 --> 00:12:11,430
That's what you desire.

344
00:12:11,497 --> 00:12:14,433
NEWBIE IN THE CLUB SCHEDULE
13:00 DOONGJI 2 DRAWING

345
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,136
TAKING A BRIEF BREAK

346
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:19,505
Open up.

347
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:21,173
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

348
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,241
RETURNING THE FORK

349
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:23,676
Thank you.

350
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:25,811
-She helped him out by his side.
-That's right.

351
00:12:25,878 --> 00:12:28,814
-She touched up his drawing.
-She helped him out with his drawing.

352
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:30,516
Isn't this what camaraderie is?

353
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:31,751
Members must get along.

354
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:32,885
He's right.

355
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:34,987
-Shall we begin Doongji 2?
-Yes.

356
00:12:35,054 --> 00:12:37,923
You will draw the answer
to the question you get

357
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:41,160
from the question card,
and then, present it like before.

358
00:12:41,227 --> 00:12:43,629
We'll give the new member
a chance to pick one.

359
00:12:43,696 --> 00:12:44,897
-Pick one?
-Pick one.

360
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,065
-One of those three?
-Yes.

361
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:47,800
-The one in the middle.
-The middle one.

362
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,301
Please read it to us.

363
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:52,671
What is it?

364
00:12:52,738 --> 00:12:54,673
"What comes to mind
when you look in the mirror?"

365
00:12:54,740 --> 00:12:56,942
WHAT COMES TO MIND
WHEN YOU LOOK IN THE MIRROR?

366
00:12:57,009 --> 00:13:00,012
-How profound.
-Oh, man.

367
00:13:00,079 --> 00:13:03,883
AGAIN, THE PEACEFUL
DRAWING TIME BEGINS

368
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:12,591
DRAWS DOONGJI 2
WHILE SIPPING TEA

369
00:13:15,995 --> 00:13:17,363
GIGGLING

370
00:13:17,429 --> 00:13:19,431
I really can't draw animals.

371
00:13:19,865 --> 00:13:21,700
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

372
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:23,202
I laughed too hard.

373
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:24,270
Don't mock me.

374
00:13:24,336 --> 00:13:25,371
CAN'T HELP BUT LAUGH

375
00:13:25,437 --> 00:13:27,039
-But it's so cute.
-It's cute.

376
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:28,741
-It's cute.
-It's so cute.

377
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:29,809
GOES BACK TO COMPLIMENTING

378
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:31,710
By the way, of all the clubs out there,

379
00:13:32,278 --> 00:13:33,679
why did you choose a drawing club?

380
00:13:33,746 --> 00:13:36,215
I used to be in another club,

381
00:13:36,282 --> 00:13:40,252
but I felt lonely after I left that club.

382
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:42,121
What was the other club?

383
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:43,322
It was a social gathering.

384
00:13:43,389 --> 00:13:45,224
Oh, a social gathering.

385
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:48,093
But it really wasn't my thing.

386
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,328
Was it overwhelming?

387
00:13:49,395 --> 00:13:51,730
It was overwhelming to deal with people.

388
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:52,798
-You got exhausted.
-Yes.

389
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:55,501
It would be tough for an introvert
to be in a club like that.

390
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:56,569
Right.

391
00:13:56,635 --> 00:13:58,604
Most of you don't seem like extroverts.

392
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:00,139
-I see a lot of introverts.
-I saw

393
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:01,540
the gathering of this club

394
00:14:01,607 --> 00:14:03,542
at a cafe twice.

395
00:14:03,609 --> 00:14:05,177
I always drew by myself,

396
00:14:05,244 --> 00:14:07,146
but then I saw these people
having fun, drawing.

397
00:14:07,813 --> 00:14:10,783
I thought that this would be
my last chance to speak to them,

398
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:14,153
so I asked if I could join the club
and that's how I ended up here.

399
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:15,855
-He asked you directly?
-Yes.

400
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:17,423
It was like street casting.

401
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:18,490
THE BRAVE GETS THE CLUB

402
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:20,726
It was as if you were drawn
to them like a magnet.

403
00:14:20,793 --> 00:14:22,728
Thankfully,
he had a nice impression of us,

404
00:14:22,795 --> 00:14:24,697
so even his younger brother joined.

405
00:14:24,763 --> 00:14:25,998
-His younger brother?
-Yes.

406
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:27,499
He brought him along.

407
00:14:27,566 --> 00:14:28,968
But you don't look alike at all.

408
00:14:30,169 --> 00:14:31,971
So that's why you're brothers.

409
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:33,038
DIFFERENT FACES, SAME HOBBY

410
00:14:33,105 --> 00:14:37,176
After my first time here,
I felt so relaxed.

411
00:14:37,243 --> 00:14:39,311
So I try to come by as often as I can.

412
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:40,379
ACTIVE BROTHER MEMBERS

413
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:43,182
My perception about
the drawing club has changed.

414
00:14:43,249 --> 00:14:46,886
What is required to qualify as a member?

415
00:14:46,952 --> 00:14:49,521
We're open and embrace everyone,

416
00:14:49,588 --> 00:14:51,390
but there's an age cut-off.

417
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:52,758
-Age cut-off?
-Actually…

418
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:54,960
CAN'T EMBRACE AGE

419
00:14:55,027 --> 00:14:56,028
You kept that quiet.

420
00:14:56,095 --> 00:14:57,096
HEALED HEART HAS BEEN BROKEN

421
00:14:57,162 --> 00:14:58,364
That's the only thing.

422
00:14:58,998 --> 00:15:00,933
Okay, Bo-ra.

423
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,301
-Wow!
-Wow.

424
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:04,203
-How pretty.
-How cute.

425
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,437
-Mirror on a cushion foundation.
-Yes.

426
00:15:05,504 --> 00:15:07,172
-The mirror on a cushion foundation?
-Wow.

427
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:10,209
We see orange mirrors
on the street, don't we?

428
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:11,610
A convex mirror.

429
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:14,013
Oh, the convex mirror for parking.

430
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:17,917
I look in the mirror
so many times a day.

431
00:15:17,983 --> 00:15:21,020
I look at it while I'm on the street
or use my phone as the mirror too.

432
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:23,188
That's how I am.

433
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:25,858
But on my way here, I thought,

434
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:28,527
"I'm heading to our club meeting.
Does my makeup look good?"

435
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,729
I checked myself while thinking that.

436
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:33,966
So this is me with my makeup on.

437
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:35,034
TITLE: CHECK MY FACE

438
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:39,438
I always wished that I had a pretty smile.

439
00:15:39,505 --> 00:15:41,507
BUT YOU ARE PRETTY NOW

440
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:44,576
You look happiest
when you're smiling, right?

441
00:15:44,643 --> 00:15:47,980
So I was hoping
that my smile appeared pretty.

442
00:15:48,047 --> 00:15:49,281
-It's pretty.
-It's what I hope.

443
00:15:49,348 --> 00:15:50,516
-Your smile's pretty.
-It is.

444
00:15:50,582 --> 00:15:51,583
It's so pretty.

445
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:52,985
You already have a pretty smile.

446
00:15:53,052 --> 00:15:54,186
-You're lovely.
-I'm embarrassed.

447
00:15:54,253 --> 00:15:55,254
You're so pretty.

448
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:57,256
Oh, I'm sorry.

449
00:15:57,323 --> 00:15:58,524
IN FRONT OF HER BOYFRIEND

450
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:00,659
I kept saying she was pretty
in front of you. I'm sorry.

451
00:16:00,726 --> 00:16:01,727
But it's true.

452
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:04,096
THEY ALWAYS END WITH COMPLIMENTS

453
00:16:04,163 --> 00:16:05,297
You look so pretty.

454
00:16:05,364 --> 00:16:06,532
What's that?

455
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:07,900
-It's a piano.
-It's a piano.

456
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,135
He drew so many things.
They look like hobbies.

457
00:16:10,202 --> 00:16:12,104
This is inside the mirror, right?

458
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:17,376
In the morning, I see various versions
of myself in a mirror.

459
00:16:17,443 --> 00:16:18,577
Then, what about the piano?

460
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,680
-I've done everything in the picture.
-You've done all of them?

461
00:16:21,747 --> 00:16:23,549
What are they? Drawing, piano, and…

462
00:16:23,615 --> 00:16:26,085
You can see me playing the piano,

463
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:27,920
playing the flute, rolling a bowling ball,

464
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,154
doing kendo,

465
00:16:29,221 --> 00:16:31,590
drawing, and cheerleading.

466
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,592
You love trying out different hobbies.

467
00:16:34,093 --> 00:16:37,730
-You mean clubs?
-He seems to love joining clubs.

468
00:16:37,796 --> 00:16:41,166
You can see your actual self in a mirror,

469
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:42,935
but you can also draw your future.

470
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:44,670
-Right.
-So this is

471
00:16:44,737 --> 00:16:46,271
-myself in the mirror.
-How cute.

472
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:48,107
How cute. You did an amazing job.

473
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:49,975
-I'm wearing a crown.
-Yes.

474
00:16:50,042 --> 00:16:51,710
I've entered this field…

475
00:16:52,611 --> 00:16:53,912
You want to become the best.

476
00:16:53,979 --> 00:16:55,014
I ought to reach the top.

477
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:57,649
That's what I hope for.

478
00:16:57,716 --> 00:16:59,718
-Age doesn't matter.
-Exactly.

479
00:17:00,285 --> 00:17:02,621
I've been on TV for some time now,

480
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:04,423
but it's only been three to four years

481
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:06,258
since I've started getting so much love.

482
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:07,326
-Really?
-Before that,

483
00:17:07,393 --> 00:17:10,029
I was slowly building myself up.

484
00:17:10,095 --> 00:17:12,631
-All of a sudden, you got popular?
-Exactly.

485
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,434
My popularity soared
about three to four years ago.

486
00:17:16,435 --> 00:17:18,437
So lately, I have been

487
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:19,872
thinking,

488
00:17:19,938 --> 00:17:21,473
"I wish this chance had come in my 20s."

489
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:22,441
FADING STAMINA

490
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:23,509
-Your energy can't…
-Yeah.

491
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:24,576
You're busy too.

492
00:17:24,643 --> 00:17:26,712
There's a limit to what I can handle now.

493
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:28,614
Yes, so,

494
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,815
I wish that

495
00:17:30,516 --> 00:17:31,950
I could have Superman-like energy.

496
00:17:32,017 --> 00:17:35,587
In the end, you need to have
a healthy mind and strong body

497
00:17:35,654 --> 00:17:38,957
to make many people laugh.

498
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:40,192
The puppy next to me is…

499
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:41,760
I've been feeling lonely lately.

500
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:44,463
I've been lonely,

501
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:47,466
so I'd like to meet someone
whose face looks like a puppy's.

502
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:48,767
Not just a puppy?

503
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:50,335
-No, not a puppy.
-Not a puppy.

504
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:52,504
A cute face like a puppy's. Woof!

505
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:56,809
I'd like to meet someone whose face
is like a cute puppy's.

506
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:59,178
That's what I'm hoping for.

507
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:00,979
It's a mirror anyway. It's not real.

508
00:18:01,046 --> 00:18:02,047
IT WON'T BE EASY TO FIND

